Tabbed layout + Dashboard KPIs + program filter

Break the long single-scroll page into 7 tabs (Dashboard, Breakdown,
Reclaim, Programs, System, Scan, Learn) with an accessible tablist
(roles, arrow-key nav, horizontal scroll on mobile). Header + privacy
promise stay pinned above the tabs.

- Dashboard: new at-a-glance KPI cards (drive used pct, free space,
  reclaimable now, biggest folder) above the gauges + advisor.
- Programs: added a name filter box.
- Demo banner gets a "Run the scan" CTA that jumps to the Scan tab.
- render() drops the results wrapper/scrollIntoView; data loads now
  switch to the Dashboard tab; Clear returns to the demo Dashboard.

All element IDs + render functions preserved. Verified live: tabs
switch, KPIs compute, filter works, resilient single-object parsing
intact, 0 network resources, CSP clean, dark/light + mobile.

